Admin Dashboard Access Control

The dashboard is protected using JWT authentication and role-based authorization.

Only users with:

role = admin

can access admin routes.

Frontend protection uses:

ProtectedRoute

with:

requiredRole="admin"

Unauthorized users are redirected to:

/
ProtectedRoute System (Updated)

The route protection system was upgraded to support:

Authentication validation
Role validation
Public routes
Dashboard isolation

The system checks:

JWT token exists
User data exists
User role matches required role

Example:

<ProtectedRoute requiredRole="admin">
  <AdminLayout />
</ProtectedRoute>
User Information Persistence

The frontend stores authenticated user data inside:

localStorage

Stored data includes:

access_token
refresh_token
user

The stored user object contains:

id
username
email
role
profile_image

This allows the frontend to:

Detect admin users
Control dashboard visibility
Render protected navigation
Avoid unnecessary API calls
