Playback restrictions
Major Problems Encountered During Development
1. ProtectedRoute TypeScript Error

Error:

Property 'requiredRole' does not exist on type 'Props'

Cause:

The ProtectedRoute component originally only accepted:

children

Solution:

The Props type was extended to include:

requiredRole?: string
2. User Data Was Null

Problem:

Admin users were redirected away from dashboard routes.

Cause:

The frontend user object was:

null

because login responses were not storing the user correctly.

Solution:

The login flow was updated to persist:

user
access_token
refresh_token

inside localStorage.

3. Teacher Endpoint 404 Error

Error:

/api/users/?role=teacher
404 Not Found

Solution:

Dedicated admin endpoints were moved into:

admin_dashboard
4. Mux Webhook Offline Errors

Error:

ERR_NGROK_3200
The endpoint is offline

Cause:

ngrok tunnel was not running.

Solution:

Started ngrok using:

ngrok http 8000
5. Mux Webhook 400 Bad Request

Cause:

Invalid webhook configuration.

Initially suspected:

MUX_WEBHOOK_SECRET

but the actual issue was:

DisallowedHost
6. Django DisallowedHost Error

Error:

Invalid HTTP_HOST header

Cause:

The ngrok domain was not added to:

ALLOWED_HOSTS

Solution:

ALLOWED_HOSTS = [
    "127.0.0.1",
    "localhost",
    "refill-doorstop-gab.ngrok-free.dev",
]

After this fix:

Webhook requests succeeded
Videos connected automatically
7. External Video Download Failure

Mux failed downloading some external videos.

Error:

download_failed

Cause:

Unsupported remote video source.

Solution:

Used verified MP4 URLs
Added future validation plans
Prioritized direct uploads
